
[1]plush

   PLUSH, n. Shag; a species of shaggy cloth or stuff with a velvet nap on
   one side, composed regularly of a woof of a single thread and a double
   warp; the one, wool of two threads twisted, the other of goat's or
   camel's hair. But some plushes are made wholly of worsted; others
   wholly of hair.
